President Biden visited the Sportrock Climbing Center in Alexandria, Virginia, where he spoke about the progress in the fight against COVID-19. He praised Governor Northam for his efforts in combating the virus and highlighted the success of the vaccination campaign. The President set a goal of getting 70% of adult Americans at least one shot by July 4th, and he urged those who have not yet been vaccinated to do so. He emphasized that getting vaccinated is easy, with many locations offering vaccinations without appointments. President Biden expressed optimism about the future and said that there is light at the end of the tunnel.